snippet.textDisplay: Don. I dont say this about any other YouTuber. However, I must say. You dont know Squat about Motor Vehicles. Every video of yours I have watched. You only knew extreme basics on the vehicle. Also, I would never allow you to touch one of my vehicles. Like in this video. Slamming the tailgate? Let me come slam your car doors. Do you realize, That by slamming doors (or in this case tailgate) Eventually it knocks the strikers out of whack. Or opening the hood from the fender. Great way to crack the fiberglass hood. Or bend a hinge. Lets talk tires. The rear tires and fenders more specific . Actually, The Fenders are serving a function.  By preventing road spray in wet conditions. Or Rocks flying off the tires. Now tires. You failed to mention. This truck, No longer had Dually tires. It had Super Single's in the rear. On to lighting. You made a poor comment as to why it had all these lights. Because it is a Commercial Vehicle. Each light does serve a purpose. Due to its height.  And other vehicles being smaller or taller. Would be a reason for 4 rows of Park or Brake and turn signals. The white lights in the rear. Are so the driver can see at night while backing up. The marker/ turn signals down the side. Are so others on the side of this truck. Can see that he is attempting to change lanes at night. Or day. Headlights. The lower lights are to actually project onto the road. As you can see. This truck is also lifted. The factory head lights may not project onto the road as well. I can go on and on. However, I think I have said enough. Do your homework. Learn about Automotive vehicles. Take a class. Get some common sense. Also, change your voice and the way you talk. It is very annoying.  Sincerely.  Me!
